node.text:
#architectsvision.
Swipe left! What do you think? 
The Lawless Retreat  The house is designed by @searllamasterhowe and is located in Jones, Michigan // Photos by @soluriphoto 
.
a forest residence tugged between trees along the edge of a state park. The Chicago-based couple had searched five years across four states to find a site for their weekend home, finally falling in love with the calm Michigan nature. With a mix of contemporary and rustic elements, the home beautifully balances the clean and raw.

#architectsvision.
Dope or nope? 
In the Austrian town of Altenmarkt im Pongau, a backyard with a retractable, terraced pool cover creates a better flexible use of the outdoor area. When retracted, one can enter the pool. When unretracted, the pool cover extends the main terrace. //l by owner @luiseperwein

How’d you describe this home?
The Doce Vida House / project designed by @ck_arquitetura_gramado and Photos by @robertagewehr 
.

#architectsvision 
Who’d you bring? 
The Woodnest Treehouse It is designed by @helenhardarchitects and is located in Odda, Norway // Photos by @ellingsensindre 
.
an extraordinary dwelling located on a steep forested hillside, suspended 5-6 meters above the forest floor and fastened it with a steel collar to the individual trunk of a living pine tree. This inevitably creates an incredible experience of the space that recalls climbing and exploring trees.

#architectsvision.
Swipe left! What do you think? 
The Venice House The home is designed by @sebastian.mariscal.studio  and is located in Venice Beach, California // Photos by Coral von Zumwalt.
.
is a 520 sqm. modern bungalow with strategically placed outdoor spaces creating harmonious transitions between indoor and outdoor. By preserving the existing trees, the house did not compromise the natural setting, but instead rises as a small garden oasis.

#architectsvision.
The serenity of the countryside! 
The Goat Mountain Ranch  The ranch is designed by @lakeflato and is located in Uvalde, Texas // Photos by @ryann_ford and @caseycdunn.
.
a residence seated on a heavily-wooded bluff with views overlooking the expansive Nueces River Valley to the southwest and upward views of Goat Mountain to the north. By using stone and reclaimed wood, the ranch is enriched by patina and history.

node.text:
#architectsvision.
The ‘Summer Residence in Pyrgos’  It is designed by Kapsimalis Architects // Photos by @g_sfakianakis 
.
 as its name suggests – a vacation home on the outskirts of the traditional village of Pyrgos in Santorini. Surrounded with vineyards and the Aegean Sea, the design of the house is based on the idea of an artificial monolithic rock placed on a random spot of the landscape, eroded by the time and natural elements.

The RLW House . The house is designed by @jacobsenarquitetura and is located in Guaruja, Brazil // Photos by @leonardofinotti 
.
a 914 sqm. home situated in the dense Atlantic Forest vegetation. One of the main focus points was to minimise the home’s footprint on the landscape, which meant that the house had to be placed as subtly as possible. Despite the five floors, the house only appears to be two-storeys, which is considered to be aesthetically more appropriate for a beach house

Describe this home in ONE word! 😍
The “House in the Landscape” isThe house is designed by @niko_architect and is located in Moscow, Russia // Photos by Vasiliy Khurtin. 
.
 an organically shaped home integrated into an artificially created landscape creating a great connection between the architecture and the open courtyard. Based on futuristic principles, the architecture evolves around the idea that everything is balanced – just like a living organism.
